1
Create package.json file
npm init

2
expres = HTTP server
morgan = HTTP logger
mongoose = NoSql DB
Multer = Upload Lib

npm i express morgan mongoose multer

3
Nodemon 
Allow app auto refresh
npm i nodemon -D

4
Go to package.json
Create a new propertie "scripts", something like this:

"scripts": {
    "dev" : "nodemon src/index.js",
    "start": "node src/index.js"
  },

Now you can use "npm run dev"
And app will reaload every time JS files change

5
Installing Multer with Amazon S3 integration
npm i multer-s3

Installing Aws-sdk. This is the integration between NODE and AWS API
npm i aws-sdk

6
Environment Variables Lib
npm i dotenv

7
npm i cors
Allow api access from diferent domain